explanation: The solution uses a "center expansion" approach, treating each character as a potential center of a palindrome and expanding outwards to count all palindromic substrings. It handles both odd and even-length palindromes by calling the helper function twice for each character. The time complexity is O(N^2) due to the nested iterations, but the space complexity remains O(1) as it only uses a constant amount of space.

